name: Gamophobia Part 1
description: Fear of commitment most often arises from childhood. Stories full of parental neglect,  abuse, and  lack of secure attachment create patterns of avoidant attachment. As a result, they learn  to be extremely independent and self-reliant at an early age. If their parents have a dysfunctional relationship or if they have only one consistent nurturing figure in their life, this will increase the likelihood of this type of problem occurring.
